.TH "attribute_container_device_trigger_safe" 9 "attribute_container_device_trigger_safe" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
attribute_container_device_trigger_safe \- execute a trigger for each matching classdev or fail all of them.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" attribute_container_device_trigger_safe
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "int (*fn)(struct attribute_container *, struct device *, struct device *) "  ","
.BI "int (*undo)(struct attribute_container *, struct device *, struct device *) "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
The generic device to run the trigger for
\fIfn\fP    the function to execute for each classdev.
\fIundo\fP  A function to undo the work previously done in case of error
.IP "fn" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "undo" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is a safe version of
attribute_container_device_trigger. It stops on the first error and
undo the partial work that has been done, on previous classdev.  It
is guaranteed that either they all succeeded, or none of them
succeeded.
